Eyes, pupils are equal, round, and reactive to light and accommodation, full range.
Marked exudative tonsillitis, non-strep, non-mono, probably mixed anaerobic infection. No significant prior history of tonsillitis.
I concur with IV clindamycin and IV Solu-Medrol as per Dr. X
I concur with IV clindamycin and IV Solu-Medrol as per Dr. X
I anticipate this patient may need several days of IV antibiotics and then be able to switch over to oral.
I do not insist that this patient will need surgical intervention since there is no evidence of abscess.
This one episode of severe tonsillitis does not mean the patient needs tonsillectomy,
